               <msContents>
                  <summary change="#add-summary">
                     An incomplete copy of an anonymous work entitled <title>Tārīkh-i Pādishāhān-i ‘Ajam</title> (History of the Emperors of Iran), an abridged history of Iran from ancient to modern times. 
                     The author apparently derived most information from the <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="">Jāmiʻ al-Tavārīkh</title> of <persName role="ant" ref="https://viaf.org/viaf/90056948/" key="person_90056948">Rashīd al-Dīn Ṭabīb (1247–1318)</persName>.
                     </summary>
                  
                  <msItem xml:id="Persian_MS_406-item1">
                     <author key="person_f407" change="#ids-cleanup">
                        <persName xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" type="anonymous">Anonymous</persName>
                     </author>
                     <editor role="ant" ref="https://viaf.org/viaf/90056948/" key="person_90056948">
                        <persName xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc">Rashīd al-Dīn Ṭabīb (1247–1318)</persName>
                     </editor>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_7136">Tārīkh-i Pādishāhān-i ‘Ajam</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_7136">تاریخ پادشاهان عجم</title>
                     <incipit xml:lang="ar" type="basmala"><locus from="1b" to="1b"> برگ ۱پ (folio 1b):</locus>
                        ستایش فروان و سنایش پیکران هنرآوار بار گاه مالک مملکی است.</incipit>
                      
                     <explicit xml:lang="fa">
                        <locus from="190b" to="190b"> برگ ۱۹۰پ (folio 190b):</locus>
                       و اجداد چنگیز خان بواسطه خون او کین پر قال ضدیت وتزاع قائم بود لاجرم در سنه تسع و ستمایت که پانزده سال از بادشاهی چترون گذاشته بود که چنگیز خان بعزم تسخیر ممالک خطای بر نشست و... </explicit>
                     <colophon>No colophon</colophon>
                     <msItem xml:id="Persian_MS_406-item1-item1">
                        <locus from="1b" to="1b">1b</locus>
                        <title>Preamble</title>
                        <msItem xml:id="Persian_MS_406-item1-item2">
                           <locus from="2a" to="2a">2a</locus>
                           <title>Chapter 1: The Ancient Persian Kings</title>
                        </msItem>
                        <msItem xml:id="Persian_MS_406-item1-item3">
                           <locus from="101a" to="101a">101a</locus>
                           <title>Chapter 2: Ancient pre-Islamic Rulers of the Arabs, Yemen, Egypt, Chaldees, Greeks, Romans, and Jews.</title>
                        </msItem>
                        <!-- After imaging, ID and add start of Chapters 3 and 4 on China, etc. -->
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                     <note>The initial portion comports with another surviving redaction held in the Royal Asiatic Society (<ref target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_2676">RAS Persian 137</ref>).</note>
                  </msItem>
                  </msItem>
